edit  
News




12 March, Iron Maiden's Ed Force One has struck a tow truck in Santiago Airport, Chile causing extensive damage to the aircraft and leading to two groundcrew being hospitalised.[1] On the band's Twitter feed it was stated that the band's shows in Chile and Argentina will not be affected by the accident.
11 March Keith Emerson best known as a rock and progressive rock and rock keyboardist with The Nice and Emerson, Lake & Palmer has been found dead at the age of 71, with a possibly self inflicted gunshot wound.[2]
5 March 2016, Based on real life Iranian Metallica fans, Iranian film Radio Dreams has won a Tiger Award at the International Film Festival Rotterdam.[3]
5 March 2016, following the end of the Canadian and ahead of the Australian leg, of their final concert tour, Black Sabbath's Tony Iommi has hinted that this might not quite be "The End", speaking a possible reunion with former front man Tony Martin.[4]
23 February 2016, members of Iranian heavy metal band Confess face possible arrest and execution for "blasphemous" lyrics.[5]
16 February 2016, the Hollywood Vampires perform a tribute at the Grammy's honouring Motorhead's Lemmy, who died late last year of cancer.[6]

