edit  
Did you know...



...that Metallica has the most grammy awards in the best heavy metal performance category and Megadeth has the record for most nominations without a win, with nine?
...that Black Sabbath is considered one of the first heavy metal bands?
...that Metallica was formed after both guitarist James Hetfield and drummer Lars Ulrich had placed advertisements in The Recycler about forming a band?
...that Ozzy Osbourne also plays the harmonica and synthesizer?
...that Dee Snider sang in several church and school choirs, including his All-State choir, as a youth?
...that Motörhead were once voted "the worst band in the world" by NME readers?





edit  
Major topics



Heavy metal artists: Black Sabbath, Iron Maiden, Judas Priest, Metallica, Led Zeppelin, Manowar


Heavy metal genres: Black metal, Death metal, Doom metal, Extreme metal, Folk metal, Glam metal, Gothic metal, Groove metal, Industrial metal, Latin metal, Medieval metal, Neo-Classical metal, Nu metal, Post-metal, Power metal, Progressive metal, Rap metal, Sludge metal, Speed metal, Stoner metal, Symphonic metal, Thrash metal, Viking metal


Instruments: Bass guitar, Drums, Electric guitar, Keyboards, Vocals





